## Limitations

The findings are based on available data and expert opinions up to October 2023. The effectiveness of vaccines can vary with new strains of viruses and changes in public health policies. Additionally, individual responses to vaccines can differ due to genetic, environmental, and health factors, which are not fully predictable. Further research and real-world data are necessary to continuously evaluate vaccine effectiveness.